                        <div style="font-size:.7rem;color:#6b7280;">Reads: hr_cash_consignments, hr_codcommission, hr_olecommissionprocess, hr_codreturncommissionprocess, hr_empcommissioneligibility, hr_employeeattendanceprocess, hr_commissionpolicy, hr_comm_insentives, hr_employeeroutecode, hr_employeelocationdetails, hr_locationmapping, hr_city</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sub-card" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Processing Logic — Step by Step</div>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li><strong>Validate:</strong> EnsureProcessesOpenAsync (month not closed). Duplicate check on <code>hr_commissionprocess</code> → "Already Processed on [date]".</li>
                <li><strong>Context:</strong> LoadCommissionProcessContextAsync — loads city's zone, station ID, all GL location IDs, employee route codes, commission rates.</li>
                <li><strong>Delete old records:</strong> DeleteCommissionRecordsAsync — removes existing <code>hr_commissionprocess</code> rows for city/month/year before re-inserting.</li>
                <li><strong>Cash rows:</strong> BuildCommissionProcessRows — reads <code>hr_cash_consignments</code> for this city's locations. Each CN mapped to the employee via route code.</li>
                <li><strong>COD rows:</strong> Reads <code>hr_codcommission</code> — aggregated COD commission per employee joined in.</li>
                <li><strong>Return COD rows:</strong> Reads <code>hr_codreturncommissionprocess</code> — aggregated return COD per employee.</li>
                <li><strong>OLE distribution:</strong> ProcessOleRecordsAsync — reads <code>hr_olecommissionprocess</code>. RateIDs 1,5 = per-employee. RateIDs 2,3,4 = proportionally distributed by working days across all employees at each location.</li>
                <li><strong>Zone classification:</strong> For each cash CN, classifies delivery zone: Local / Same Zone / Other Zone. Applies different commission rate per zone.</li>
                <li><strong>Rate lookup:</strong> hr_commissionpolicy (IsPercent=1 → percentage of amount; IsPercent=0 → flat per-CN rate).</li>
                <li><strong>Eligibility check:</strong> hr_empcommissioneligibility WHERE IsEligible=TRUE — only eligible employees get commission rows.</li>
                <li><strong>Working days:</strong> From hr_employeeattendanceprocess — TotalDays − Sundays − Absences + Adjustments.</li>
                <li><strong>Insert commission rows:</strong> InsertCommissionRowsAsync → bulk insert into <code>hr_commissionprocess</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Insert adjustments:</strong> BuildCommissionAdjustments → <code>hr_empcommadjdtl</code> with Adjustment_Type_id=3 (excludes types 1,2).</li>
                <li><strong>Acknowledgment:</strong> InsertCommissionAcknowledgmentAsync → <code>hr_acknowledgment</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Commit.</strong></li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="section-grid" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Zone Classification Logic</div>
                <div style="background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:.5rem;padding:.65rem .8rem;font-family:monospace;font-size:.73rem;color:#166534;line-height:1.7;">
                    IF(Station_id = dest_City_id, 'Local',<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;IF(Zone = OvernightZone, 'Same Zone',<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'Other Zone'))
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:.72rem;color:#64748b;margin:.5rem 0 0;">Zone and OvernightZone from <code>lcs.city</code> and <code>lcs.zone_color</code> (LHR_Billing). Each zone tier has a separate commission rate in hr_commissionpolicy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Working Days Formula</div>
                <div style="background:#eff6ff;border:1px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:.5rem;padding:.65rem .8rem;font-family:monospace;font-size:.73rem;color:#1e40af;line-height:1.7;">
                    WorkingDays = TotalDays<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;− Sundays<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;− Absences<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Adjustments
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:.72rem;color:#64748b;margin:.5rem 0 0;">Source: <code>hr_employeeattendanceprocess</code>. Used as denominator in OLE proportional distribution (RateIDs 2,3,4).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-grid" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Hardcoded Values</div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">21</span><span class="hc-desc">CommissionStartDay — period start (defined in PayrollService.Commission.cs:14)</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">20</span><span class="hc-desc">CommissionEndDay — period end (line 15)</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">−1</span><span class="hc-desc">CommissionStartDiff — AddMonths(−1) for from-date (line 16)</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">IsEligible = TRUE</span><span class="hc-desc">Filter on hr_empcommissioneligibility — only eligible employees get commission records.</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">Adjustment_Type_id NOT IN (1,2)</span><span class="hc-desc">Adjustments of type 1 and 2 are preserved; only type 3+ are deleted/recreated by Master step.</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">type=1</span><span class="hc-desc">hr_acknowledgment record type inserted by Commission Process Master step.</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Output Tables</div>
                <table class="info-table">
                    <tr><th>Table</th><th>DB</th><th>Content</th></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_commissionprocess</code></td><td>lcs_hr</td><td>Final commission per employee per source type</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_empcommadjdtl</code></td><td>lcs_hr</td><td>Commission adjustment breakdown rows</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_acknowledgment</code></td><td>lcs_hr</td><td>Audit record (type=1)</td></tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Preview Mode callout -->
        <div style="background:#fffbeb;border:1px solid #fde68a;border-radius:.6rem;padding:.75rem 1rem;margin-top:1rem;font-size:.78rem;color:#92400e;">
            <strong><i class="fas fa-eye" style="margin-right:.4rem;"></i>Preview Mode:</strong>
            PreviewCommissionProcessAsync runs the full processing logic inside a transaction that is <strong>always rolled back</strong>.
            Output is returned to the caller for review. The <code>RollbackIntegrityPreserved</code> flag confirms no data was written.
            This allows "what-if" analysis without affecting the live database.
        </div>
    </div><!-- /body-c5 -->
</div>

