<!-- COMMISSION 6 — EMPLOYEE COMMISSION REPROCESS (Manual Tool)    -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="comm-card theme-amber">
    <div class="comm-header" onclick="toggleComm('c6')">
        <div class="comm-icon"><i class="fas fa-user-cog"></i></div>
        <div>
            <div class="comm-title">Employee Commission Reprocess</div>
            <div class="comm-subtitle">Manual correction tool — NOT part of the 6-step automation pipeline</div>
        </div>
        <div class="comm-badges">
            <span class="badge-sm" style="background:#fef3c7;color:#92400e;border:1px solid #fde68a;">Manual Tool</span>
            <span class="badge-sm" style="background:#fee2e2;color:#991b1b;border:1px solid #fecaca;">Not Automated</span>
        </div>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down comm-toggle" id="toggle-c6"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="comm-body" id="body-c6">

        <!-- Why not in automation -->
        <div style="background:#fffbeb;border:1px solid #fde68a;border-radius:.6rem;padding:.75rem 1rem;margin-top:1rem;font-size:.78rem;color:#92400e;">
            <strong><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle" style="margin-right:.4rem;"></i>Why not in the automation pipeline?</strong>
            This tool is designed for <strong>post-pipeline individual correction</strong> — when a single employee's commission is wrong due to a data fix, attendance correction,
            or route code change. Running it for all employees automatically would be redundant with Step 5 (Master). It is intended for
            targeted, on-demand reprocessing of one employee at a time. Accessible at <code>/Payroll/EmployeeCommissionReprocess</code>.
        </div>

        <div class="section-grid" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Overview</div>
                <p style="font-size:.78rem;color:#334155;margin:0;">
                    Recalculates commission for a <strong>single employee</strong> (identified by 14-digit zero-padded EmpNo)
                    without affecting any other employees. Reuses the same logic as the Master Commission step but scopes
                    all DELETE and INSERT operations to only the target employee's rows.
                    Requires all pipeline steps (1–6 including Final Commission) to have been run first.
                </p>
                <div style="margin-top:.65rem; display:flex; gap:.4rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
                    <span class="tag tag-yellow">Single Employee</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-blue">Scoped DEL/INS</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-gray">Requires Full Pipeline</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-key"></i> Input &amp; Prerequisites</div>
                <table class="info-table">
                    <tr><td class="label">Input</td><td>Employee Number (14-digit, zero-padded, e.g. <code>00000000012345</code>), Year, Month</td></tr>
                    <tr><td class="label">EmpNo format</td><td><code>varchar(14)</code>, zero-padded. All lookup tables use this exact format.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td class="label">Prerequisite</td><td>Steps 1 (Cash), 2 (COD), 3 (OverLand), 4 (Return COD), 5 (Master) must be complete for that month/city</td></tr>
                    <tr><td class="label">City resolution</td><td>Employee's city code is auto-resolved via <code>hr_employeelocationdetails</code> (ToDate IS NULL)</td></tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sub-card" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Processing Logic — 12 Steps</div>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li>Resolve employee's city code from <code>hr_employeelocationdetails JOIN hr_city ON station_id</code>.</li>
                <li>LoadCommissionProcessContextAsync — loads full city context (same as Master step).</li>
                <li>LoadCommissionEmployeePopulationAsync — loads ALL employees in the city. <em>Required so OLE proportional distribution uses the correct total working-days denominator.</em></li>
                <li>AppendOleDataForSingleEmployeeAsync — loads OLE data. RateIDs 2,3,4 are read without employee filter (pool amounts). RateIDs 1,5 and RBI are filtered to target employee's routes only.</li>
                <li>AggregateEmployeeCommission — aggregates all OLE components by (emp_no, cour_id).</li>
                <li>BuildCommissionProcessRows — builds cash rows for the city. MergeCashRowsIntoEmployees matches by emp_no.</li>
                <li>Filter to ONLY target employee's rows before any write operation.</li>
                <li><code>DELETE FROM hr_commissionprocess WHERE month=&#64;M AND year=&#64;Y AND emp_no=&#64;EmpNo</code> — scoped delete, does NOT touch other employees.</li>
                <li>InsertCommissionRowsAsync — inserts only the target employee's rows.</li>
                <li><code>DELETE FROM hr_empcommadjdtl WHERE ... AND emp_no=&#64;EmpNo AND Adjustment_Type_id NOT IN (1,2)</code></li>
                <li>INSERT adjustment rows for target employee (Adjustment_Type_id=3).</li>
                <li>INSERT <code>hr_acknowledgment</code> type=3. Commit.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="section-grid" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Hardcoded Values</div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">varchar(14)</span><span class="hc-desc">EmpNo format in all 4 lookup tables (hr_commissionprocess, hr_empcommadjdtl, hr_employeeroutecode, hr_employeelocationdetails). Must be 14-digit zero-padded.</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">NOT IN (1, 2)</span><span class="hc-desc">Adjustment_Type_id exclusion in DELETE — adjustments of type 1 and 2 are manually-entered overrides that must not be wiped.</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">type=3</span><span class="hc-desc">hr_acknowledgment record type for Employee Commission Reprocess (mirrors old EmployeeCommissionProcess.aspx.cs).</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">CodeType=9</span><span class="hc-desc">Filter for OLE RateID 1 (Credit Booking) — same as OverLand step.</span></div>
                <div class="hc-row"><span class="hc-val">NOT IN (3,10,11)</span><span class="hc-desc">Filter for OLE RateIDs 5, 8, 84–95 — same as OverLand step.</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-card">
                <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Tables Read &amp; Written</div>
                <table class="info-table">
                    <tr><th>Table</th><th>Operation</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_employeelocationdetails</code></td><td>READ</td><td>City resolution for emp_no</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_employeeroutecode</code></td><td>READ</td><td>Route-to-employee mapping</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_olecommissionprocess</code></td><td>READ</td><td>OLE data already computed by Step 3</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_cash_consignments</code></td><td>READ</td><td>Cash data already computed by Step 1</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_commissionprocess</code></td><td>DELETE + INSERT</td><td>Scoped to emp_no only</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_empcommadjdtl</code></td><td>DELETE + INSERT</td><td>Scoped to emp_no, excludes types 1,2</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>hr_acknowledgment</code></td><td>INSERT</td><td>type=3 audit record</td></tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div><!-- /body-c6 -->
</div>

