        <div class="sub-card" style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <div class="sub-title"><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Processing Logic — Step by Step</div>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li><strong>Validate month open:</strong> EnsureProcessesOpenAsync — rejects if month already closed in <code>hr_closeprocesses</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Duplicate check:</strong> Queries <code>is_final_commission_process</code> for city/month/year. If exists → throws "Already Processed on [date]. By: [user]".</li>
                <li><strong>Date range check:</strong> toDate (20th of current month) must be ≤ today. Rejects if commission period has not yet ended.</li>
                <li><strong>Resolve station IDs:</strong> Queries <code>hr_locationmapping JOIN lcs_setup.locations JOIN hr_city</code> to get BStationId list for the city. Fails if none found.</li>
                <li><strong>Open MIS connection:</strong> Opens a separate MySqlConnection to lcs_incentive &#64; 172.16.0.7. Begins transaction.</li>
                <li><strong>Call stored procedure:</strong> <code>CALL lcs_incentive.ProcessFinalCommission(city, stationsCsv, fromDate, toDate, userId)</code></li>
                <li><strong>If rows &gt; 0:</strong> Commits MIS transaction. Continues to lock insert.</li>
                <li><strong>If rows = 0:</strong> Rolls back MIS transaction. Returns Success=true with ProcessedCount=0. No lock inserted. Automation marks this as <strong>NoData</strong> — city stays out of done-count, auto-resets on next run.</li>
                <li><strong>Insert lock:</strong> INSERT into <code>is_final_commission_process (city, month, year, userId, created_at)</code> — prevents future re-processing via duplicate check (step 2).</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

